Package it.uniroma2.sel.simlab.jeqn.specialNodes

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AllocateNode
    Implements an EQN Allocate node.
    AllocateReleasePoolOfTokens
    Implements a Pool of Token for couples of Allocate - Release Nodes
    CreateDestroyPoolOfTokens
    Implements a pool of tokens for couples of Create - Release Nodes
    CreateNode
    Implements a EQN Create Node, that is the entity that requests to a CreateDestroyPoolOfTokens the creation of a token
    DestroyNode
    Implements a EQN Destroy node, that is the entity requesting the destruction of a token to a CreateDestroyPoolOfTokens
    ForkNode
    Implements the EQN ForkNode, that is the node that generates a set of child users that are to be synchronized at a specified Join node.
    JoinNode
    Implements the Join Node simulation entity.
    OperationNode
    Performs a specified operation upon the reception of a user.
    OperationNode_OLD
    Same as Operation Node, but in its previous (old) version.
    PassiveQueueInNode
    Defines the common structure for nodes (Allocate and Create) that regulate the access to a passive queue zone
    PassiveQueueOutNode
    Defines the common structure for nodes (Release and Destroy) that delimits a passive queue zone
    PoolOfTokens
    Defines the general structure and interface for PoolOfTokens (e.g.
    QoSUpdater  
    ReleaseNode
    Implements the EQN Release Node, that is the entity that returns the tokens to a specified Pool of Tokens when users leave the passive queue zone
    SetNode<T>
    Implements the EQN Set node.
    SpecialNode
    Defines the structure and the interface of entities that are introduced in the Extended Queueing Network domain, with respect to the Queueing Network domain.
    SplitNode
    Implements the EQN split node.
    SplitNode_UserTracker
    Implements a EQN Split Node that also offers User Tracking capabilities.
